---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
			<main>
				<section class="about">
					<h4>About Me</h4>

					<p>
					I am Agyapong Gyamfi, a Cloud Security Engineer focused on securing
					AI agents, MCP servers, and the cloud infrastructure they depend on.
					</p>

					<p>
					My background combines cloud engineering, cybersecurity, DevSecOps,
					enterprise technical support, databases, networking, and production
					troubleshooting. I have worked across regulated and mission-critical
					environments where uptime, clear communication, security controls,
					root-cause analysis, and documentation matter.
					</p>

					<p>
					I am strongest where infrastructure, security, and operations overlap:
					diagnosing complex issues, understanding how systems fail, designing
					safer access paths, automating repeatable work, and translating technical
					problems into clear action.
					</p>

					<h4>My current direction</h4>

					<p>
					My career focus is cloud security and DevSecOps, with a growing
					specialization in AI infrastructure security. As organizations adopt
					AI agents, MCP servers, automated workflows, and cloud-connected tools,
					the security questions become more important: What can the agent access?
					Where are secrets stored? How are cloud roles assumed? How are actions
					logged? How are CI/CD pipelines protected? How do we detect abuse?
					</p>

					<p>
					Those are the problems I am positioning myself to solve: securing the
					infrastructure, identities, pipelines, data paths, and operational controls
					behind modern cloud and AI-enabled systems.
					</p>

					<h4>What I work on</h4>

					<ul>
					<li>Cloud security architecture and secure AWS infrastructure patterns</li>
					<li>IAM, role assumption, trust policies, certificates, and identity boundaries</li>
					<li>Terraform, CloudFormation, CI/CD automation, and configuration consistency</li>
					<li>Monitoring, logging, incident response, RCA, and operational hardening</li>
					<li>API security testing, traffic analysis, and production troubleshooting</li>
					<li>AI agent, MCP server, and AI infrastructure security research</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>How I got here</h4>
					<p>
					My path runs through enterprise technical support, cloud engineering, and cybersecurity — years of incident response, systems troubleshooting, and clear technical communication under pressure, across databases, networking, Linux and Windows, and multi-cloud environments. That operational background is why I approach security as something that has to work in production, not just satisfy a checklist: I've been the person restoring service at 2 a.m., and it shows in how I design controls.
					</p>

					<h4>Why I write</h4>

					<p>
					This site is where I document practical lessons from the work I do and
					the skills I am building. I write about architecture decisions, security
					tradeoffs, mistakes, fixes, and the reasoning behind hardening modern
					infrastructure.
					</p>

					<p>
					For confidentiality and security reasons, I do not publish sensitive
					implementation details from employer, client, or production environments.
					Instead, I focus on transferable lessons, safe technical patterns, and
					practical explanations that demonstrate how I think through cloud,
					DevSecOps, and security problems.
					</p>

					<h4>For recruiters and hiring teams</h4>

					<p>
					I am a strong fit for roles involving cloud security, DevSecOps,
					infrastructure automation, production troubleshooting, and emerging AI
					infrastructure security. I bring hands-on technical execution, support
					discipline, security awareness, and the ability to explain complex systems
					clearly.
					</p>

					<p>
					<center><i><a href="/resume">View my resume</a> | <a href="/projects">review my projects</a>.</i></center>
					</p>
				</section>
			</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

